Share prices plunged in early trade as anopening foreign exchange record low of 143.75 yen to the dollarand a weak stockmarket in New York withered investors'confidence, brokers said.    After 32 minutes' trade, the average plummetted 313.00 to22,609.20. Yesterday the market gained 9.21 to a record close.    Brokers said the dollar's fall against the yen prompted alarge selloff of export-related shares. But fears had spreadthroughout the market, depressing almost all issues. REUTER&#3;